body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Cooper Security Solutions. My name is Terry Cooper. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello Terry, my name is Kathleen Griffin.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Kathleen. Can you please provide me with your date of birth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my date of birth is the twenty-second of September, nineteen eighty-eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Kathleen. Could you also provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, the last four digits of my phone number are five six seven eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Kathleen. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I'm feeling relieved now. Thank you for your help, Terry.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Kathleen. If you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Thank you for your time. Have a great day!

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Terry. You too, have a great day!
